  "text": "Researchers have proposed alternative mechanisms to explain these discrepancies of monomer penetration model. Blankschtein and associates utilized radiolabeled 14 C to track the amount of SDS penetrated into epidermis and found it to increase with SDS concentration when applied above the CMC [CITATION_1] . When polyethylene oxide (PEO) was added to the SDS solution, less SDS was observed in the epidermis. PEO primarily interacts with micelles but not with monomers. The PEO-bound SDS micelles have an average radius of 25Å, while that of the unbound micelles is ∼20Å. It was suggested that SDS micelles, with its small size, could be capable of penetrating the skin through aqueous pores, while the larger PEO-bound SDS micelles could not and a surfactant micelle skin penetration model was proposed. While the current research is actively evaluating this micelle model, it has already inspired new technologies to think outside of the box of CMC-based cleanser design approach.",
